','1','','A0',1),('1016','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程旨在幫助學生對未來論文撰述之相關議題做更深入完備之探討。課程中，學生必須與該專業領域相關專長之教師共同訂訂學習契約並透過輔導達成學習目標。','The purpose of this course is to help students to gain knowledge related to an identified research topic. The student will be evaluated based on the pre-arranged learning objectives in the learning contract.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授。修課限制：本所碩士班（婦女組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11163','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1017','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（精神組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11164','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1018','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（兒童組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11166','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1019','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（專師組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11168','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('102','觀光休閒健康產業進階實習','Advanced Practice in leisure, tourism and health promotion industries','本課程旨在增進休閒旅遊健康促進之工作專業能力，輔導學生進入未來將就業的產業環境，結合理論與實務，有效考量職場環境協助設計休閒健康促進企劃方案，並進而瞭解健康休閒機構的管理策略。','This course aims to equip students with the ability to put professional knowledge on leisure, tourism and health promotion into further practice. Their on-site training can be extended to a future career in the field. Students will learn how to propose plans for leisure and health promotion tailored to their working environment. They will also be exposed to the management of health and leisure organizations.','修課限制：實習課程、提前開課(2/1-7/31)。畢業班課程。','全18週',1132,'23140','4','專業選修(系所)','3','1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9','','41',9),('1020','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（護資組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11167','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1021','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（社區組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11165','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1022','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（老人組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11162','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1023','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11161','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1024','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（婦女組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11163','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1025','高等資料分析方法論','Advanced Biostatistics','Biostatistics plays an essential role in all stages of a quantitative health care research from design through to analysis and interpretation. This course covers the essential principles and methods required for a Ph.D. degree. During this Advanced Biostatistics course, students will build on the basic statistical skills they gained in introductory statistics courses and learn to apply more advanced techniques to real data. Emphasis is on study design, appropriate analysis, software (SPSS) application and interpretation of results. The underlying concepts of statistical analysis are covered. Sessions include lectures and practical work, both computer-based and using small workshops for discussion.\r\nStatistical analyses will be performed using SPSS and Excel. Microsoft Word is required for all written assignments (output from SPSS and Excel should be copy/pasted into Word).','Biostatistics plays an essential role in all stages of a quantitative health care research from design through to analysis and interpretation. This course covers the essential principles and methods required for a Ph.D. degree. During this Advanced Biostatistics course, students will build on the basic statistical skills they gained in introductory statistics courses and learn to apply more advanced techniques to real data. Emphasis is on study design, appropriate analysis, software (SPSS) application and interpretation of results. The underlying concepts of statistical analysis are covered. Sessions include lectures and practical work, both computer-based and using small workshops for discussion.\r\nStatistical analyses will be performed using SPSS and Excel. Microsoft Word is required for all written assignments (output from SPSS and Excel should be copy/pasted into Word).','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','1','專業必修(系所)','1','6,7,8','F603','A0',3),('1026','高等質性研究方法論','Advanced Qualitative Research','此課程主要為質性研究方法論之介紹與練習，學生能了解質性研究之發展，典範 與方法論，進而能運用質性研究練習收集資料，分析資料及批判質性研究，期使 學生能有執行質性研究之專題經驗。課程內容包含：質性研究之典範，紮根理論， 現象學，各類質性研究之比較，質性研究之收集資料，分析資料，嚴謹度，批判， 撰寫等。','This course critically examines diverse qualitative approaches applied in research. The discussion emphasizes on philosophical bases of qualitative inquiries, whereas the analysis focuses on paradigmatic nature of qualitative approaches in contrast to quantitative approaches.  The class presents sampling and a variety of data collection procedures; discusses issues on rigor; explores methods of analysis appropriate to the data; and considers ethical issues associated with each stage of the research. Students are expected to complete a qualitative project.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.、全英語授課','全18週',1132,'11870','1','專業必修(系所)','2','6,7,8','B603','A0',3),('1027','進階護理實務','Advanced Nursing Practicum','This course aims to provide nursing doctoral students to obtain clinical or research experiences at health related institutions. Based on familiar with clinical issues, students will analyze and interpret the current development of nursing science, involve the related practice. In this course, students engage in a 144-hour advanced practicum in theory-guided practice in a selected domain of nursing. Concurrently, students participate in two seminars to present the progress of practicum and clinical experiences, and the theoretical and evidence based nursing care model.','This course aims to provide nursing doctoral students to obtain clinical or research experiences at health related institutions. Based on familiar with clinical issues, students will analyze and interpret the current development of nursing science, involve the related practice. In this course, students engage in a 144-hour advanced practicum in theory-guided practice in a selected domain of nursing. Concurrently, students participate in two seminars to present the progress of practicum and clinical experiences, and the theoretical and evidence based nursing care model.','1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','1','專業必修(系所)','4','8,9','B603','A0',2),('1028','介入性與臨床試驗研究方法論','Design and Analysis of Nursing Intervention Studies','This course is designed to familiarize students with theory-driven nursing intervention research and clinical trials, including design, conduct, analysis and interpretation of results. Topics will include commonly used designs, methods for randomization, blinding and sample size determination, choice of controls, collaborative/ multicenter trial requirements and operational issues, data management and data quality issues, interim analysis methods, critical review of clinical trial results, ethics considerations and statistical techniques for analyzing clinical trial and nursing intervention data.','This course is designed to familiarize students with theory-driven nursing intervention research and clinical trials, including design, conduct, analysis and interpretation of results. Topics will include commonly used designs, methods for randomization, blinding and sample size determination, choice of controls, collaborative/ multicenter trial requirements and operational issues, data management and data quality issues, interim analysis methods, critical review of clinical trial results, ethics considerations and statistical techniques for analyzing clinical trial and nursing intervention data.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','4','6,7,8','B635','20',3),('1029','進階護理實務統計與應用','Advanced Statistic Approaches and Applications in Nursing Research','隨著護理研究的現代化發展，如何根據臨床資料計算出一些有意義的數據，並利用這些數據去推論與瞭解事實，進而有助做出正確的推論與建議。本課程之目標係希冀培養學生護理量化研究之進階實務能力，進而具備現代化護理數量方法之全面觀。 課程設計將著重於數量實務模擬，針對特定主題選定適當模式完成分析，得到有效支持探討主題之結論。課程內容方面涵蓋中介變項回歸分析、交互作用分析、統合分析、多層次臨床資料分析、臨床試驗、預測與評估等多種分析技術。此外，並配合文獻標竿學習、實例個案討論報告，期使學生能夠瞭解應用方向與方式。','The focus of this course is on nursing and health related research traditions, the relationship between modern statistic paradigms and research designs and how various breakthrough statistics have been used by nurse researchers.  Advanced assumptions, developments, limitations, and advantages of modern statistic approaches in the context of clinical nursing phenomena will be addressed.\r\nWe emphasize the applications of nursing statistic methods and introduce matrices as they appear and show how they simplify the presentation of nursing research models and techniques. Statistical packages (such as SAS, SPSS) provide the numerical results to complex analysis.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','4','3,4','F603','21',2),('103','觀光休閒健康產業進階實習','Advanced Practice in leisure, tourism and health promotion industries','本課程旨在增進休閒旅遊健康促進之工作專業能力，輔導學生進入未來將就業的產業環境，結合理論與實務，有效考量職場環境協助設計休閒健康促進企劃方案，並進而瞭解健康休閒機構的管理策略。','This course aims to equip students with the ability to put professional knowledge on leisure, tourism and health promotion into further practice. Their on-site training can be extended to a future career in the field. Students will learn how to propose plans for leisure and health promotion tailored to their working environment. They will also be exposed to the management of health and leisure organizations.','修課限制：實習課程、提前開課(2/1-7/31)。畢業班課程。','全18週',1132,'23140','4','專業選修(系所)','4','1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9','','41',9),('1030','領導與決策','Leadership and Decision Making','The purpose of this course is designed to assist students to exercise the problem handling and team work ability, and go through by teaching method, criticism and debate, special subject report, introspection and feedback. The content including: The leadership style of leader and manager, strategy and policy making, problem handling, organization culture and change, conflict management, medical treatment system, team cooperation, and case analysis, to improve their capability of leadership and make decision.','The purpose of this course is designed to assist students to exercise the problem handling and team work ability, and go through by teaching method, criticism and debate, special subject report, introspection and feedback. The content including: The leadership style of leader and manager, strategy and policy making, problem handling, organization culture and change, conflict management, medical treatment system, team cooperation, and case analysis, to improve their capability of leadership and make decision.','114/02/25課程停開\n修課限制：\n 1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','3','2,3,4','','22',3),('1031','論文專題研究I','Dissertation Independent Study I','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據博士生未來護理專業發展方向，引導學生探索護理實務相關之研究議題，進行相關理論及照護模式之分析，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，與產官學界等多方領域先進之討論，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、進行或完成研究計畫之撰寫。','This course is conducted through individualized instruction and is designed to guide doctoral students in exploring research topics relevant to their future nursing professional development. It involves the analysis of pertinent theories and care models, integration of their clinical expertise, application of critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, and engagement in discussions with experts from various sectors including academia, industry, and government. The course aims to help the student determine his/her research direction and topic, formulate research designs, and initiate or complete the writing of a research proposal.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','6','1','','A0',1),('1032','博士論文I','Dissertation I','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助博士生以臨床實務或護理專業發展為基礎，應用相關理論、照護模式及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析、研究成果報告發表及博士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction with the aim of assisting the doctoral student who is building upon his/her clinical practice or nursing professional development. It emphasizes the application of relevant theories, nursing care models, and research skills, the execution of research projects, data analysis, publishing of the results of studies, and the writing of his/her dissertation.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','3','專業必修(系所)','6','2','','A0',6),('1033','論文專題研究II','Dissertation Independent Study II','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據博士生未來護理專業發展方向，引導學生應用相關核心概念，發展護理相關理論及照護模式，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，確認研究主題及設計、完成博士論文研究計畫之書寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, tailored to the doctoral student’s future development in the field of nursing. It guides the student to apply relevant core concepts, develop nursing-related theories and nursing care models, integrate his/her clinical expertise, employ critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, and confirm his/her research topic and designs. It culminates in the completion of a written research proposal for his/her dissertation.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','3','專業選修(系所)','6','1','','A0',1),('1034','論文專題研究III','Dissertation Independent Study III','','','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','3','專業選修(系所)','6','3','','A0',1),('1035','博士論文II','Dissertation II','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助博士生以臨床實務或護理專業發展為基礎，應用相關理論、照護模式及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，完成博士論文之撰寫。','This course is conducted through individualized instruction with the objective of assisting the doctoral student who is building upon his/her clinical practice or nursing professional development. It focuses on the application of relevant theories, nursing care models, and research skills, the execution of research projects, data analysis, and the completion of the dissertation.','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11870','4','專業必修(系所)','6','1','','A0',6),('1036','研究方法論','Research Methodology','本課程的內容訓練學生如何做一個科學性的研究，必須有一套訓練的方法，舉凡在如何尋找問題，如何解決問題，如何搜集資料，如何分析資料等都需要有一套嚴謹的方法論，最後介紹研究報告、論文之撰寫。','This course introduces the study methods of conducting an investigation for graduate students. This course includes mining a problem, solving the problem, collecting the data for the problem, and analyzing the data. How to writing a report and paper will','1.全英語授課\n This class is taught in English.2.Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11860','1','專業必修(系所)','5','2,3,4','B128','A0',3),('1037','專題研究','Independent Study','','','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11860','1','專業選修(系所)','6','1','','A0',1),('1038','進階護理 I','Advanced Practice Nursing I','','This course provides students with fundamental knowledge necessary to deliver advanced nursing care for adults and children. This course aims to increase students\' understanding of the major concepts and related theories of advanced practice nursing. The focus is on the management of specific care issues relevant in adult and children. The roles and function of the advance practice nursing will be integrated throughout the course. Through lectures, discussions, and reports, students will expand their knowledge and competency in managing common health conditions of adults and children complementary to the essence of advanced nursing practice.','修課限制：\n 1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n 2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11860','1','專業必修(系所)','3','6,7,8','B128','A0',3),('1039','進階護理實作','Field Experience of Advanced Practice Nursing','','This course is aimed to increase students\' understanding of the major concepts and related theories \r\nof advanced practice nursing. The focus is on the management of mental health issues as well as the \r\ncommunity health. The course will provide students with fundamental knowledge necessary to \r\ndeliver advanced nursing care for clients with mental health conditions as well as for clients in the \r\ncommunity settings. The roles and function of advance practice nurses will be integrated throughout \r\nthe course. Through lectures, discussions, and reports, students will expand their knowledge and \r\ncompetency for managing common mental health issues and community health by integrating \r\nevidenced-based nursing and their clinical experiences.','修課限制：\n 1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n 2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1132,'11860','2','專業必修(系所)','3','2,3,4','B128','A0',3),('104','觀光休閒健康產業進階實習','Advanced Practice in leisure, tourism and health promotion industries','本課程旨在增進休閒旅遊健康促進之工作專業能力，輔導學生進入未來將就業的產業環境，結合理論與實務，有效考量職場環境協助設計休閒健康促進企劃方案，並進而瞭解健康休閒機構的管理策略。','This course aims to equip students with the ability to put professional knowledge on leisure, tourism and health promotion into further practice. Their on-site training can be extended to a future career in the field. Students will learn how to propose plans for leisure and health promotion tailored to their working environment. They will also be exposed to the management of health and leisure organizations.','修課限制：實習課程、提前開課(2/1-7/31)。畢業班課程。','全18週',1132,'23140','4','專業選修(系所)','5','1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9','','41',9),('1040','碩士論文','Master thesis','','','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.、全英語授課','全18週',1132,'11860','2','專業必修(系所)','6','1','','A0',6),('1041','健康照護實務創作','The Ergonomics Project of Health Care','本課程主要探討健康照護及日常生活中，人們所使用的物品及環境的實務設計創作，透過人因工程之介紹與護理實務所發現之問題結合，以分組討論與設計製作的方式，讓健康照護需求透過設計探討將之落實，期使理論能與實務相互結合外並希望藉由跨學門之不同經驗與專長解決健康照護職場之相關健康照護設計。','This course provides students to have the concept and practice of well-being design for health care and daily living. The major focus of the course encompasses: the concepts of Ergonomics and health care, and the practice of well-being design. Students pr','1140220關課，修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、老人組、婦女組、精神組、社區組、兒童組、護資組、專師組、中西醫組）、本所國內博士班、外所國內碩士班（是否列入畢業學分，請參照入學年課程科目表）','全18週',1132,'11461','1','專業選修(系所)','4','12,13,14','','10',3),('1042','成人健康照護 I','Health Care of Adult I','本課程旨在增進學生照護成人健康之護理專業能力。成人病患常見的健康問題之臨床實務面，學生須統整並運用所學之內外科護理學、生理病理學、病因學、臨床診斷學、身體評估以及管理學等相關理論。藉由整合學理和臨床實務，學生能增強成人個案照護與治療等相關的學理，且能展現醫療團隊的溝通協調，以達成本課程的目標。','The purpose of the course is to advance the clinical professional competence in acute care setting. Students will be able to apply knowledge and theories of medical-surgical nursing, patho-physiology, etiology, clinical diagnosis, physical assessment, and management. Application of theories into clinical practice and coordination of health care team effectively to manage adults’ health problems will accomplish the course objectives.','02/06、02/12寒假提前上課，修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組）','全18週',1132,'11461','1','專業必修(系所)','5','5,6,7','B603','A0',3),('1043','成人健康照護實習 I','Health Care of Adult I - Practicum ( 162 hours )','本實習課程目的在增進學生照護成人個案之專業能力。實習中，學生將針對成人健康照護之相關主題，有組織、有系統的應用並驗證相關理論、研究、教育於臨床實務。學生在實習中能展現進階護理師的角色與功能，並完成相關方案，以達成本課程之目標。','The purpose of the course is to advanced clinical professional competence of students in acute care setting. Within the practicum, student will focus on issues that related to adult care, organizing and systemically applying and examining theories, research, education, and counseling in advanced practice. The course objectives will be accomplished by demonstrating advanced practice roles and competence in completing a related project, demonstrating advanced practice roles and competence in completing a related project.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（成人組）','全18週',1132,'11461','1','專業必修(系所)','6','14','','A0',3),('1044','社區衛生照護 I','Advanced Community Health Care I','本課程旨在引導學生進入社區，由個人、家庭、團體等層面來瞭解其健康理念及行為，並藉此協助學生發展其進階的社區健康專業能力。本課程強調以社區相關之知識、理論及研究做為學生未來實際操作之基礎。','The course is designed to guide the students to enter the community, and understand the health beliefs and behaviors from individual, family and aggregate perspectives. This will serve as foundation for the advanced practice in community. The course emphasizes on the community related knowledge, theories, and researches as the bases for student’s future practice in community','修課限制：本所碩士班（社區組）','全18週',1132,'11465','1','專業必修(系所)','5','5,6,7','G104','A0',3),('1045','社區衛生照護實習 I','Community Health Nursing I practicum','本課程旨在協助學生應用社區護理的理論與模式於真實社區情境中。學生在課程結束時須能獨力完成社區評估、確認社區健康需求或診斷，並能排定健康需求的優先次序，統整社區資源並能與社區建立夥伴關係。','The course is designed to provide an opportunity for students to apply the theories and models in a real community. At the end of the course, the students will be able to develop the concept of community assessment, define the community diagnoses, and the priority, integrate the community resources and establish the partnership with the community.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（社區組）','全18週',1132,'11465','1','專業必修(系所)','6','14','','A0',3),('1046','研究方法論','Research Methods and Design in Nursing','本課程的內容訓練學生如何做一個科學性的研究，必須有一套訓練的方法，舉凡在如何尋找問題，如何解決問題，如何搜集資料，如何分析資料等都需要有一套嚴謹的方法論，最後介紹研究報告、論文之撰寫。','This course introduces the study methods of conducting an investigation for graduate students. This course includes mining a problem, solving the problem, collecting the data for the problem, and analyzing the data. How to writing a report and paper will','修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、老人組、社區組）、本所碩士班研二以上（重修生不限組別）','全18週',1132,'11461','1','專業必修(系所)','5','2,3,4','B603','A0',3),('1047','婦女健康照護 I','Health Care for Women I','此課程要旨在於增進學生照顧婦女的臨床專業能力、健康促進的理論與行為以及婦女臨床專家角色，學生在此課程中將選擇一個與婦女健康相關主題，有組織的統整、應用並驗證相關的理論及研究於臨床實務，同時學生必須針對所選擇的婦女議題及護理應用，發展基本護理概念架構。','The purpose of this course are to provide an in-depth analysis of the context in which women health is practiced, of theories and behaviors relevant to health promotion, and the advanced nursing practice role in women health. Concepts, theories and practices related to health promotion in women health will be discussed. Students’ ability to analyzed, apply and evaluate relevant theories/research in clinical situations are emphasized. Students are expected to develop a preliminary conceptual model to explain a clinical phenomenon involving women and its implications in nursing.','修課限制：本所碩士班（婦女組）','全18週',1132,'11463','1','專業必修(系所)','5','5,6,7','G103','A0',3),('1048','婦女健康照護實習 I','Health Care for Women I - Clinical Practicum','此課程要旨在於增進學生照顧婦女的臨床專業能力，包括生育及其他健康問題，學生在此課程中將選擇一個與婦女健康相關主題，有組織的統整、應用並驗證相關的理論及研究於臨床實務，同時學生必須針對所選擇的婦女議題及護理應用，發展基本護理概念架構。契約學習是臨床教學的主要策略。','This course is designed to assist students acquiring clinical expertise in nursing care of clients with obstetric, gynecologic and other female gender specified health problems. In this course, students are required to select a problem or an issue discussed in the seminar and complete the nursing process through integration and application of the theories for selected clients in appropriate clinical settings. Students are expected to develop a preliminary conceptual model to explain a clinical phenomena involving women and its implications in nursing. Problem solving and critical thinking skills of students will be enhanced by employing the learning contract teaching strategy in the course.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（婦女組）','全18週',1132,'11463','1','專業必修(系所)','6','14','','A0',3),('1049','護理資訊管理 I','Nursing Information Management I','本課程旨在於提升學生瞭解護理資訊管理相關理論與概念架構及其應用，學生能瞭解護理資訊學於臨床照護、管理、教學及研究上的使用情況。課程內容包括護理資訊管理專業人員在護理科技運用之選擇考量、及教育訓練過程與臨床照護使用的評值、旁及於有關電子化護理照護及護理資訊實務的範疇及標準。','The purpose of this course is to assist students in identifying the major theories and models of information management within nursing practice. Students will be able to understand the application of nursing informatics on clinical care, education, research and management. The nursing information specialist roles in the system selection and evaluation, education strategies, technology use in care evaluation, and the introduction of e-nursing is also included. Additionally, the future trends of the development of nursing informatics scope and standards of practice are identified as well.','修課限制：本所碩士班（護資組）','全18週',1132,'11467','1','專業必修(系所)','5','5,6,7','B635','A0',3),('105','休閒與健康資訊研究及應用','Seminar on Information Studies and Application in Leisure and Health','本課程旨在探討資訊科技與休閒健康相關議題，鼓勵學生運用資訊知識和技能，培養同學在資訊科技進步的時代裡熟悉程式語言之操作與應用，能夠瞭解前瞻資訊科技的應用。','This course encourages students to use advanced information technology knowledge and skills, try to become the scene design content creators, training students with advanced information technology and practical ability. And be familiar with the operation and application of the programming language.','修課限制：\n1.程式設計課程、本所一般生、外所本國生(是否列入畢業學分，請參照入學年課程科目表)、跨校 。\n2.為鼓勵學生修讀程式設計課程，有關「休閒與健康資訊研究及應用」2學分與「多變量解析」2學分為二擇一必選修課程，請於畢業前務必擇一修課。','全18週',1132,'23160','1','專業選修(系所)','4','6,7','F604','10',2),('1050','護理資訊管理實習 I','Practicum of Nursing Information Management I','此課程旨在使學生能應用護理資訊管理學於臨床科技使用之情境分析。學生需瞭解資訊科技如何運用於臨床病人照護，並分析相關臨床照護資訊科技使用之議題。同時，學生需應用相關護理資訊管理理論與概念架構於一特定護理科技應用系統分析與設計，並探討護理資訊護如何滿足臨床照護者、護理管理者、護理教育者及其未來發展；旁及於參與系統使用過程的教育訓練與評值、及瞭解系統設計如何受到健康照護潮流衝擊的影響。','This course provides students an opportunity to analyze the current situations of nursing information management. Learning activities include applying a related theory or concept analysis in design and development of a project to investigate a nursing information technology application on meeting identified needs and trends in nursing students, clinicians, administrators, nursing faculty and patients and families. Students will participate in planning, education and evaluation of the implementation of a nursing information system, and to identify the impact of selected trends on the design of nursing information systems. Students will also address current and future clinical issues on selected nursing information technologies on health care.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（護資組）','全18週',1132,'11467','1','專業必修(系所)','6','14','','A0',3),('1051','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（兒童組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11466','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1052','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授。修課限制：本所碩士班（護資組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11467','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1053','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11461','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1054','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（老人組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11462','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1055','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授。修課限制：本所碩士班（婦女組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11463','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1056','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（社區組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11465','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1057','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（精神組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11464','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1058','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（專師組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11468','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('1059','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（老人組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11462','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('106','旅遊餐飲與健康專題','Seminar of Tourism, Food and Health','隨著國民健康意識抬頭，遊客旅遊時不再只是享受美食，如何吃得健康也是旅遊者關注的議題。由於旅遊時的飲食營養會影響遊客的健康與旅遊品質，因此本課程結合旅遊、餐飲、營養與飲食文化等內容，藉以討論旅遊之餐飲與健康。主要課程內容說明如下: (一)旅遊與營養:旅遊中六大類食物與營養素、營養標示、每日飲食指南與食物代換表在健康飲食上之應用; (二)旅遊餐飲衛生與安全:旅遊飲食衛生之注意事項與食物中毒之預防; (三)慢性疾病遊客之飲食:糖尿病、高血壓、高血脂、痛風、腎臟病等患者旅遊時之營養照顧; (四)飲食文化與營養:討論各國不同的飲食文化與餐食營養。','As people are becoming more health conscious, tourists are no longer just seeking for gourmet food while traveling, but also caring about healthy eating. Diet while travelling affects both health and travel quality. Therefore, this course combines information concerning travel, nutrition, health, and culture to explore the experience of enjoying food &amp; beverages while traveling abroad. The main topics covered in this course are the followings: (1) Travel &amp; Nutrition: The six essential categories of food and their nutritional content, introduction to nutritional labeling, and daily dietary guidelines; (2) Food &amp; Beverage Sanitation and Safety While Travelling: Precautions for food hygiene and prevention of food poisoning while travelling; (3) Diet for Tourists with Chronic Diseases: Nutritional care for Tourists travelling with diabetes, hypertension, high cholesterol, gout, kidney or other diseases; (4) Food Culture and Nutrition: A discussion of different food cultures and the nutritional content of their diets.','修課限制：\n本所一般碩士班、外所本國生（是否列入畢業學分請參照入學年課程科目表）、跨校。','全18週',1132,'23160','1','專業選修(系所)','4','8,9','F9021','10',2),('1060','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（婦女組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11463','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1061','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（社區組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11465','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1062','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（專師組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11468','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1063','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（兒童組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11466','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1064','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（護資組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11467','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1065','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11461','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1066','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（精神組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1132,'11464','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('1067','性別與健康照護','Gender and Healthcare','本課程以性別主流化的概念為基礎，透過個體啟蒙、意識覺醒與行為實踐的過程，將引導學生論述於不同醫學專科領域之性別議題，且能辨識家庭、工作職場、社會福利和醫療環境中的性別平等政策。以期使學生能發展具有性別平等的概念，並應用於健康照護的情境中。','This course is based on the concept of gender mainstreaming. We hope that through the process of enlightenment, awareness and practice that could help student to understand the gender perspective in different area of medical specialties, and to identify the relation for gender concept among family, workplace, social welfare, and health policy. The student would develop the vision and ability of gender analysis, and take action with gender perspective which applies in nursing care.','修課限制：本系二技進修部、護理學院全。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業選修(系所)','1','6,7','F607','10',2),('1068','安寧照護','Palliative and Hospice Care','本課程主旨在建立學生緩和與安寧照護的概念與認知。藉由了解末期疾病病人身、心、社會的衝擊及面對死亡的準備，體認多科專業團隊與義工團隊在末期疾病照護的協同合作功能。以增進學生對疾病末期病人及其家庭身心社會照顧及協助病人及其家屬面對死亡的準備。課程中，亦同時探討護理人員在照顧末期病人時所面臨的壓力與倫理困境。','The design of this course is aimed to increase students’ understanding about concepts of palliative care and hospice care, and advance their competence of caring for the terminally ill patients and their family. The physical and psychosocial impact of ter','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本所(本國生)、護理學院全3年級以上、學士後。2/26停開。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業選修(系所)','1','6,7','','11',2),('1069','反射療護理論與實務','reflexology theory and practice','本課程旨在培育學生執行反射療護之知識、技能與態度。課程內容包括反射療護之歷史、相關理論、於健康促進之應用及反射療護之技術操作。本課程首重反射療護之實務操作，學生須具有實踐及操作之能力，於課程結束時，通過認知和技術考試。','This is an introduction course of hand and foot reflexology. The aim of the course is to offer students a fundamental understanding of theories and skills of reflexology. The course integrates the knowledge, skills and attitude of reflexology by the means','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生、護理學院全、學士後。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業選修(系所)','1','8,9','G101','12',2),('107','旅遊醫學與健康專題','Issue on travel medicine and health','本課程旨在從旅遊醫學之角度闡明廣泛性之旅遊休閒與健康相關之總體概念，俾使學習者對其有所了解與體認。學習者將透過課程講授、分組報告與交互討論，研討旅遊休閒與健康相關之理念、模式、價值、原則與方法，以及了解旅遊休閒對健康之正負面效應。本課程也輔導研究生就現行旅遊健康議題加以討論，以為爾後進入旅遊休閒與健康有關職場之經營管理、指導、教育訓練以及研究等預作準備。','This gateway course intentionally and extensionally highlights the overall &amp; general figure of travel medicine and the impact on health. Through facilitating lectures and discussions, the learners could approach the concepts, values, principles and methods of the above topics, and increasingly understand the effects of travel and leisure toward health. Alongside, this course provides the students with a discussion on the current popular topics of health and tourism, and thus fulfills the one of the objectives of integrating theory and practice which is helpful in future studies and research for the students.','修課限制：\n所一般碩士班、外所本國生(是否列入畢業學分，請參照入學年課程科目表)、跨校。','全18週',1132,'23160','1','專業選修(系所)','2','3,4','F9021','10',2),('1070','中醫照護應用','Application of Traditional Chinese Medicine in Care','本課程旨在介紹我國具有民俗特色之保健活動—刮痧、拔罐、按摩推拿、灸法、耳穴保健和養生健身法。學生除了學習傳統民俗保健方法有關的基本理論之外，並藉著練習不同的技術，習得調身（姿勢）、調心（意識）及調息（呼吸）的技術，鍛鍊自己的精、氣、神，達到疏通經絡、增強抵抗力，促進自己及他人的健康層次，培養學生對中醫使用開放之態度，並將所學應用於專業照護上。','This course is to offer students the necessary knowledge and skills of Chinese traditional care methods. It is based upon the traditional theories of Ch\'i, blood, visceral organs, meridians and collateral. In additional to traditional theories and techniques of scraping, cupping, massage, moxibustion, ear acupuncture and Ch\'i exercises will be demonstrated. Students are required to understand the theories and to practice the techniques learned from the class in order to adjust their mind and breathing, to improve the flow of Ch\'i and blood, to regulate the functions of visceral organs, and strengthen the resistance, promote the health of oneself and others, cultivate students\' open attitude to the use of traditional Chinese medicine, and apply what they have learned to professional care.','修課限制：\n1.跨域課程。\n2.本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生、外系二技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技進修、學士後。\n3.志願選開放10個外系名額，第二階段開放全校，邀請業師進行專題講座。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業選修(系所)','1','6,7','G405','13',2),('1071','日文基礎(一)','Basic Japanese','台灣目前正處於一個多元文化交融並存的時代，學習多種語言、文化是一種未來的趨勢。除英語 之外，日語的重要性已浮出抬面。對日據時代老一輩台灣人而言，日語有一種回憶童年的親切感，雖 然在光復後，和日本文化、語言保持了很長一段的疏離，但在近年媒體開放之後，來自日本的各種大 眾文化，開始出現在日常生活大小層面中，此時對日本文化的親進態度又回歸到現代年輕人身上，這 種「哈日」的想法，成為學習語言最有趣的動機，藉而看到日本文化的更深層面是件很好的事。','The purpose of this course is to teach students the basics of Japanese. From the fundamental 50 pronunciations to greetings &amp; conversions commonly used at hospitals, students will need to practice conversations and readings. An increasing number of Japanese in Taiwan had mad learning Japanese as the second foreign language a high priority for health care staffs. After this course, students will be able to use practical Japanese and read the instructions from Japanese medicine.','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、外系二技進修部、本系四技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技一般生','全18週',1132,'11230','1','通識選修(通識)','1','6,7','G403','90',2),('1072','日文基礎(二)','Japanese Basis II','台灣目前正處於一個多元文化交融並存的時代，學習多種語言、文化是一種未來的趨勢。除英 語之外，日語的重要性已浮出抬面。對日據時代老一輩台灣人而言，日語有一種回憶童年的親 切感，雖然在光復後，和日本文化、語言保持了很長一段的疏離，但在近年媒體開放之後，來 自日本的各種大眾文化，開始出現在日常生活大小層面中，此時對日本文化的親進態度又回歸 到現代年輕人身上，這種「哈日」的想法，成為學習語言最有趣的動機，藉而看到日本文化的 更深層面是件很好的事。','The purpose of this course is to teach students the basics of Japanese. From the fundamental 50 pronunciations to greetings &amp; conversions commonly used at hospitals, students will need to practice conversations and readings. An increasing number of Japanese in Taiwan had mad learning Japanese as the second foreign language a high priority for health care staffs. After this course, students will be able to use practical Japanese and read the instructions from Japanese medicine.','修課限制：\n1.本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生、本系二技進修部、外系二技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技進修部。\n2.為避免學習銜接問題，本課程需具備基礎發音，讀、寫平片假名之程度，請選修同學評估自身學習狀況加退選。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','通識選修(通識)','1','8,9','G403','91',2),('1073','中國詩詞欣賞','Chinese Poetry','本課程主要藉由晚唐五代詩、兩宋詞之選讀，兼顧婉約、豪放風格，不主一家的作品，從而指導學生研讀及賞析的方法，使學生掌握先賢之生命智慧與藝術心靈，了解中國學術源流及古今文學的精義，從而體認傳統文化的歷史傳承之責任。','The main purpose of this course is to increase students’ capabilities of appreciating literary works and expressing verbally. Through studies of representative works of poems and Ci, students are guided to cultivate their interest in these classic works by reading, intoning, appreciating and evaluating.','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、外系二技進修部、本系四技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技一般生','全18週',1132,'11230','1','通識選修(通識)','1','8,9','G105','92',2),('1074','生物統計學','Introduction of Biostatistics','授與提昇研究能力與增進閱讀學術文獻有關統計能力之知識與概念。其內容包括敘述統計學（集中趨勢量數、離中趨勢量數、分布、作圖與作表）以及推論統計學（區間估計與考驗之過程，Z score、pooled-t test、paired-t test、卡方、one-way ANOVA、皮爾遜積差相關、線性迴歸與無母數分析等）。課中利用EXCEL資料分析工具及各式小型科學電算器如Casio 36PV等協助運算，期能達成理論與實務之結合為目的。','This course is to offer fundamental statistical concepts related to the practice of nursing. The contents include population &amp; samples descriptive statistics; probability; sampling; statistical distributions; estimation; hypothesis testing; pooled samples','修課限制：本系二技進修部、跨校','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','1','3,4','B210','A0',2),('1075','研究概論','Introduction to Nursing Research','本課程旨在提供學生基本的研究知識與技能。學生除了對實務情境產生質疑，並藉由討論、批判、觀摩等活動，提升團隊合作、問題解決和批判性思考等能力。課程內容包括研究與專業發展間的關係、研究基本概念、研究步驟、研究計畫的撰寫和研究文獻的批判。','This course is an introductory course on nursing research. Students will have the opportunity for a systematic investigation of a health-related topic of the student’s interest demonstrating knowledge and skills of research methodology. This course provid','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生三年級以上、外系二技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技進修部、學士後、本所本國生、外所本國生、（研究生下修，不計入畢業學分）、跨校','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','2','1,2','G107','A0',2),('1076','病理學','Pathology','病理學是探討疾病的原因、機轉、病理變化及過程、預後等的一門學問 課程分二大部分1.概論2.各論。 概論主要介紹外來的傷害與疾病的刺激對細胞與組織所造成的共通的變化、與反應與機轉。詳細內容包括細胞傷害與死亡、炎症與癒合、細胞生長發育的異常、體液代謝障礙、免疫與腫瘤、遺傳、代謝與營養疾病。 各論討論各器官系統其各類疾病的致病原因、機轉，病理變化及臨床表現等。詳細 的內容包括心臟血管系統疾病、呼吸系統疾病、肝臟及膽管系統疾病、消化系統及 胰臟疾病、內分泌系統疾病、血液與淋巴系統疾病、腎臟疾病、男性生殖系統疾病、','The scientific focus of pathology is on the etiology of disease, the mechanisms of pathogenesis, and the pathways by which morphologic changes occur. Pathogenesis of diseases will be discussed on the molecular basis to facilitate the understanding of diff','1.修課限制：本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生二年級以上、本系學士後、本系二技進修部、外系二技一般生、外系四技一般生二年級以上、外系二技進修部、跨校。\n2.本課程建議有解剖學、生理學、微生物免疫學基礎者可修。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','2','8,9','B113','A0',2),('1077','環境永續與資訊科學','Environmental Sustainability and Information Science','本課程為環境永續發展與資訊科學之教學內容，主要在闡述環境永續發展的重要性，提昇學生永續發展的覺知，結合資訊科技的應用，以具備適當資訊應用的能力，培養維護環境永續的行動技能。\r\n課程內容涵蓋環境倫理、環境變遷與防災、節能減碳與能源管理、生態保育、電腦程式設計、結合環境教育主題之資訊應用等主題。教學策略運用做中學、在真實的情境中體驗、合作學習法、運用感官學習、探索環境與結合電腦軟體應用等議題。','This course comprises instructional content on environmental sustainability and information science, primarily elucidating the significance of environmental sustainability, enhancing students\' awareness of sustainable development, integrating the application of information technology to possess appropriate information application abilities, and fostering actionable skills for maintaining environmental sustainability.','1.第二階段加退選，開放修習「環境教育/電腦軟體整合應用/環境永續與資訊科學」課程之學生及重修生互相跨班選課。 2.全部網路選課，無紙本加選。 3.因轉學轉系或修習雙聯學位同學如欲提早修課，經中心同意後於第三階段開放其選課，名單會於第二階段選課結束後送交教務處。1-8週上課地點F601及第9-16週上課地點G204。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','通識必修(通識)','1','1,1,2,2','F601,G204','A0',2),('1078','藥理學','Pharmacology','本課程之設計係以二技護理系學生為授課對象，課程內容著重於培養護理專業實務照護能力；故以深入淺出之方式探討藥物於人體中之藥理作用機轉，並介紹與臨床應用有關之藥品動力、交互作用及藥物中毒之解毒等，課程單元內容包括：藥理學概論、自主神經系統作用劑、影響內分泌及新陳代謝藥物、中樞神經作用劑、心臟血管疾病用藥以及化學療法藥物等。','This pharmacology is a two credit hour course and designed especially for nursing. This curriculum emphasizes on the clinical applications and action mechanisms of various drugs. The curriculum training will start from more details and bring a completely concepts. The subjects include general concepts of pharmacology and pharmacokinetic, autonomic nervous system, autacoids, cardiovascular system, central nervous system, microbial disease, neoplastic disease related drugs.','1.修課限制：本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生二年級以上、本系二技進修部、本所本國生、（研究生下修，不計入畢業學分）、學士後。\n2.先修課程：生理學。','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','2','6,7','B113','A0',2),('1079','關懷與溝通','Caring and Communication','本課程旨在增進學生對自我的認識，進而培養學生溝通與關懷的專業能力，內容包含人與自我、人與社會、人與環境、人與靈命、關懷的藝術、關懷與護理、人際溝通的特質、模式與相關影響因素，知覺與溝通、觀察技巧、語言溝通，傾聽與同理心的應用。課程結構強調自我的省思及使學生能於設計的模擬情境中融合溝通與關懷的知識、技能與態度，展現專業能力。課程內涵以認識自我之關懷心及溝通型態，瞭解他人對自我的看法，進而分析自我的關懷心及溝通型態對自己生活及執行專業角色時的影響，並願意改變過去不合適的溝通型態，展現關懷心及溝通技巧於生活情境','The aims of the course are to improve the self- awareness of the student, to nurture the competence of communication and caring. The course contents include the relationships among people to people, people to society, people to environment and spirit. The','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、外系二技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技進修部、學士後','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','2','3,4','G107','A0',2),('108','健康環境專題','Seminar in Healing Environments','健康/療癒環境研究與設計近來成為熱門議題，同時亦被認為能增進健康與關懷環境的方向，本課程從旅遊健康的角度介紹，主要內容包括療癒環境歷史與文化觀、健康/療癒相關作用機轉(如旅遊環境類型中之環境偏好、環境認知及其生心理反應效益等)、健康/療癒環境設計哲學、各族群使用者健康/療癒情境、健康/療癒旅遊環境相關研究等。','Healing Environment Research and Design has recently become a hot topic, but also considered the direction of sustainable environment. This course introduces the environment from the perspective of tourism and health, the main contents include historical and cultural of healing environment concept, related to the mechanism of action of healing (such as tourism and environment types of environmental preferences, environmental awareness and effectiveness of physiological-psychological, etc.), environmental design philosophy of healing, healing environment of various groups, tourism environment-related research.','修課限制：本所碩士一般生、外所(本國生/是否列入畢業學分，請參照入學年課程科目表)、跨校。','全18週',1132,'23160','1','專業選修(系所)','2','6,7','F9021','10',2),('1080','生物統計學','Introduction of Biostatistics','授與提昇研究能力與增進閱讀學術文獻有關統計能力之知識與概念。其內容包括敘述統計學（集中趨勢量數、離中趨勢量數、分布、作圖與作表）以及推論統計學（區間估計與考驗之過程，Z score、pooled-t test、paired-t test、卡方、one-way ANOVA、皮爾遜積差相關、線性迴歸與無母數分析等）。課中利用EXCEL資料分析工具及各式小型科學電算器如Casio 36PV等協助運算，期能達成理論與實務之結合為目的。','This course is to offer fundamental statistical concepts related to the practice of nursing. The contents include population &amp; samples descriptive statistics; probability; sampling; statistical distributions; estimation; hypothesis testing; pooled samples','修課限制：本系二技進修部','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','1','1,2','B210','B0',2),('1081','研究概論','Introduction to Nursing Research','本課程旨在提供學生基本的研究知識與技能。學生除了對實務情境產生質疑，並藉由討論、批判、觀摩等活動，提升團隊合作、問題解決和批判性思考等能力。課程內容包括研究與專業發展間的關係、研究基本概念、研究步驟、研究計畫的撰寫和研究文獻的批判。','This course is an introductory course on nursing research. Students will have the opportunity for a systematic investigation of a health-related topic of the student’s interest demonstrating knowledge and skills of research methodology. This course provid','修課限制：本系二技進修部、本系二技一般生、本系四技一般生三年級以上、外系二技一般生、外系四技一般生、外系二技進修部、學士後、本所本國生、外所本國生、（研究生下修，不計入畢業學分）、跨校','全18週',1132,'11230','1','專業必修(系所)','2','3,4','G402','B0',2),('1082','病理學','Pathology','病理學是探討疾病的原因、機轉、病理變化及過程、預後等的一門學問 課程分二大部分1.概論2.各論。 概論主要介紹外來的傷害與疾病的刺激對細胞與組織所造成的共通的變化、與反應與機轉。詳細內容包括細胞傷害與死亡、炎症與癒合、細胞生長發育的異常、體液代謝障礙、免疫與腫瘤、遺傳、代謝與營養疾病。 各論討論各器官系統其各類疾病的致病原因、機轉，病理變化及臨床表現等。詳細 的內容包括心臟血管系統疾病、呼吸系統疾病、肝臟及膽管系統疾病、消化系統及 胰臟疾病、內分泌系統疾病、血液與淋巴系統疾病、腎臟疾病、男性生殖系統疾病、','The scientific focus of pathology is on the etiology of disease, the mechanisms of pathogenesis, and the pathways by which morphologic changes occur. Pathogenesis of diseases 