點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1141,'11161','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('232','英語聽講練習三','Freshman English Lab III','本課程包括每週2小時1學分的英語聽與講練習。學生經程度測驗後依程度分級。教學重點為初中級至中級(low-intermediate ~ intermediate level)之日常生活會話英語聽力理解及練習。','This is a one-semester course which is worth one credit and includes a two-hour listening and speaking practice in the language laboratory each week. The main contents of the course consist of listening comprehension of everyday English conversations (from high beginning to low-intermediate level) and English conversation practice.','1.建議同學依排定時程修習課程避免延畢，如遇特殊原因須停修者，須先至通識中心進行前置流程。2.第二階段加退選開放健科學院重修生選課。3.第三階段加退選開放系外重修生選課。4.全英語授課。','全18週',1132,'21140','1','通識必修(通識)','4','1,2','B216','23',1),('2320','碩士論文','Thesis','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助碩士生以臨床實務為基礎，應用護理理論及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，並完成研究成果報告及碩士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, aiming to assist the master\'s student in utilizing clinical practice as a foundation. It focuses on the application of nursing theory and research skills, the execution of research protocol, data analysis, and the completion of research outcome reports and the master\'s thesis.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（專師組一般生）、書面選課','全18週',1141,'11168','2','專業必修(系所)','7','2','','A0',6),('2321','護理資訊管理 II','Nursing Information Managemetn II','本課程的目的在提升學生暸解資訊科技在健康照護機構的應用及推展過程。學生可暸解資訊科技發展的策略計畫、機構組織改變及健康照護上的應用狀況及其相關議題。課程內容包括資訊科技推動策略的應用、組織的改變過程、資訊科技的整合、資訊科技推動成效及相關議題，旁及於健康資訊隱私及安全議題之探討。','The purpose of this course is to assist students in identifying the major concepts information management within healthcare organizations. Students will be able to understand the application of information technology on strategic planning in consultation, organizational change process, care transformation and evolution, the development of and the evaluation of care outcome. Issues of nursing ingormation management and data privacy and patient safety will be explored as well.','修課限制：本所碩士班（護資組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11167','2','專業必修(系所)','5','2,3,4','B635','A0',3),('2322','護理資訊管理實習 II','Practicum of Nursing Information Managemetn II','此課程的目的使學生透過科技應用的專案模式，瞭解實習機構中推動護理資訊系統的過程，並探討資訊科技運用於健康照護的成果或專案管理的議題。同時能運用實證文獻，提出資訊科技於特定護理領域應用的相關研究議題。','This course offers students an opportunity to synthesize their information nursing management knowledge and apply it on their interested clinical field for quality improvement. Learning activities include developing a project management process of any technology use for outcome measurement, staff management or usage experiences. Students will explore related research issues in system design and development, project management, user experiences,healthcare process and organizational management.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（護資組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11167','2','專業必修(系所)','7','5','','A0',3),('2323','科學哲學與知識發展','Philosophy of Science and Knowledge Development','本課程旨在培養學生探索、批判、分析與建構護理知識之能力。主要學習經驗包括 區辨及探討科學哲學的演進與知識建構之型式，科學的哲理、批判理論以及探討及評值 概念的建構及理論的發展。透過相互的研討，期能使護理博士學生能從科學哲學與知識 認識層面，探討其所關注的護理議題，且應用理論或概念建構發展與實務議題有關之護 理理論或概念模式。','This course aims to provide students with the skills to investigate, assess, and analyze nursing knowledge. The learning experience involves the exploration of the development of science philosophy and of nursing knowledge. The course is a research and discussion experience aimed at enabling doctoral graduate students to become knowledgeable about approaches to studies of scientific knowledge development. Forces affecting the development of knowledge, the origins of key terms and concepts, and the identification of nursing issues related to epistemology and the philosophy of science identification will also be explored.','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n 1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.本所國內博士班一年級、本所國際博士班一年級 \nEligible students include first-year students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level) and first-year students of domestic doctoral programs in nursing','全18週',1141,'11870','1','專業必修(系所)','2','2,3,4','B603','A0',3),('2324','高等量性研究方法論','Advanced Quantitative Research Methods','本課程為進階量性研究方法論；課程在探討實證護理應用於實務及不同的研究設計方 法之特性及優缺點，並進一步介紹各個研究步驟之重點及相關議題。學生將依指引檢驗與 批判已發表於專業期刊當中之研究文獻，學習發表研究報告之重點；以期未來能以此知識 為基礎，完成完善的量性研究計畫。','This course addresses theoretical basis of advanced quantitative methods. Focus of the course is placed on the importance of nursing research in evidence-based practice. Various research designs, research steps and related issues will be thoroughly discussed. Based on the guidance, students are required to critique papers published in well-known journals. After completion of the class, students will learn to appreciate a research paper, report the research findings, and develop their research plans in the near future.','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n 1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English.\n 2.本所國內博士班一年級、本所國際博士班一年級 Eligible students include first-year students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level) and first-year students of domestic doctoral programs in nursing','全18週',1141,'11870','1','專業必修(系所)','4','6,7,8','B636','A0',3),('2325','測量工具的發展與建構','Measurement and Instrumentation','This course aims to provide comprehensive knowledge of the theory and foundation which underlies measurement process, current measurement and measurers of frequently used in health-related inquiry, and to promote their ability in applying principles of instrument development to current measurement problem. Course contents include theories of measurement, psychometric quality of research instruments, strategies for designing measures, measurement issues in health-related inquiry, and application of principles of instruments development in research study.','This course aims to provide comprehensive knowledge of the theory and foundation which underlies measurement process, current measurement and measurers of frequently used in health-related inquiry, and to promote their ability in applying principles of instrument development to current measurement problem. Course contents include theories of measurement, psychometric quality of research instruments, strategies for designing measures, measurement issues in health-related inquiry, and application of principles of instruments development in research study.','修課限制 Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.可選學生為護理所國際博士班二年級以上學生、護理所國內博士班二年級學生 Eligible students include second-year and higher-level students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level) and second-year students of domestic doctoral programs in nursing. \n3.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools.','全18週',1141,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','4','2,3,4','B635','20',3),('2326','系統性文獻回顧與統合分析','Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis','本課程為系統性文獻回顧與統合分析及實務實作，旨在應用實證步驟於研究及實務。課程介紹系統性文獻回顧實證健康照護、組織及計畫系統性文獻回顧、文獻搜尋技巧的原則及資源、評析文獻、資料萃取及處理、統合分析。課程實務實作包含運用學習小組進行實作練習，進一步執行相關主題資料萃取及統合分析之實務操作。','The course Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis addresses the steps of Systematic review and meta-analysis in the nursing research and the evidence in nursing practice. Focus of the course is planced on the evidence-based nursing care，organizing and planning a systematic review，key princuples，resources and techniques for searching the literature，critical appraisal appraisal，introduce deta extraction and managment，introduce Meta-Analysis. For the practice，the course is also placed on the deta extraction，management and analysis for RCT and observational research design.After completion of the ，students will learn to develop a specific issue related systematic review and Meta-Analysis to nursing practice.','1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English.\n2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n3.可選學生為護理所國際博士班學生 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level)','全18週',1141,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','2','7,8,9','F603','21',3),('2327','論文專題研究I','Dissertation Independent Study I','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據博士生未來護理專業發展方向，引導學生探索護理實務相關之研究議題，進行相關理論及照護模式之分析，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，與產官學界等多方領域先進之討論，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、進行或完成研究計畫之撰寫。','This course is conducted through individualized instruction and is designed to guide doctoral students in exploring research topics relevant to their future nursing professional development. It involves the analysis of pertinent theories and care models, integration of their clinical expertise, application of critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, and engagement in discussions with experts from various sectors including academia, industry, and government. The course aims to help the student determine his/her research direction and topic, formulate research designs, and initiate or complete the writing of a research proposal.','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n 1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English.\n 2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools.\n 3.本所國際博士班可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level)\n 4.書面選課 Registration will be done by paper application using the form generated from the system','全18週',1141,'11870','2','專業選修(系所)','6','1,2','','A0',1),('2328','環境與健康政策','Environment and Health Policy','本課程在提供學生對環境與健康政策的整體觀，從預防保健的角度分析國內及國際的環境與健康政策議題，並重新定位健康與環境政策原則。學生可針對各國健康政策的推動、健康服務品質的保障、國內外政府與非政府之健康組織與資源的整合與運用等議題進行分析與討論，針對上述健康政策議題提出需求評估、計畫評值或成果評價。','This course is aimed to provide a holistic view of health services. Social, economic, and political influences on environment and health policy internationally and nationally are analyzed from a political economy perspective. Students critique and debate a variety of health care reforms to enhance quality, assure access, and improve cost efficiency. The application of nursing research in outcome studies, program evaluation, and needs assessment is explored.','\"修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n 1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.本所國內博士班二年級、本所國際博士班二年級 Eligible students include second-year students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level) and second-year students of domestic doctoral programs in nursing.\"\"\"','全18週',1141,'11870','2','專業必修(系所)','4','5,6,7','B635','A0',3),('2329','博士論文I','Dissertation I','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助博士生以臨床實務或護理專業發展為基礎，應用相關理論、照護模式及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析、研究成果報告發表及博士論文之撰寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction with the aim of assisting the doctoral student who is building upon his/her clinical practice or nursing professional development. It emphasizes the application of relevant theories, nursing care models, and research skills, the execution of research projects, data analysis, publishing of the results of studies, and the writing of his/her dissertation.','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n3.本所國際博士班可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level)\n4.書面選課 Registration will be done by paper application using the form generated from the system.','全18週',1141,'11870','3','專業必修(系所)','6','1,2','','A0',6),('233','進階英文','Advanced English','本課程為一學期兩小時兩學分的課程。教學重點為文法重點複習、閱讀技巧及練習、普通英文文章閱讀，於該課程中學生能熟練中級至中高級(intermediate ~high intermediate level)基本文法重點、學習並運用各種英文閱讀技巧、閱讀並理解中級至中高級(intermediate ~high intermediate level)英文文章。','This is a two-credit, one-semester course. Included in the instruction for students of all levels are grammar review, basic sentence structure, introduction and application of English reading skills to high-intermediate reading articles, outlining and summarizing, as well as general or professional conversational English, talks, lectures, reports, and programs.','1.建議同學依排定時程修習課程避免延畢，如遇特殊原因須停修者，須先至通識中心進行前置流程。2.第二階段加退選開放健科學院重修生選課。3.第三階段加退選開放系外重修生選課。','全18週',1132,'21140','1','通識必修(通識)','4','3,4','B216','23',2),('2330','論文專題研究II','Dissertation Independent Study II','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據博士生未來護理專業發展方向，引導學生應用相關核心概念，發展護理相關理論及照護模式，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，確認研究主題及設計、完成博士論文研究計畫之書寫。','This course is structured as individualized instruction, tailored to the doctoral student’s future development in the field of nursing. It guides the student to apply relevant core concepts, develop nursing-related theories and nursing care models, integrate his/her clinical expertise, employ critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, and confirm his/her research topic and designs. It culminates in the completion of a written research proposal for his/her dissertation.','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n3.本所國際博士班可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level)\n4.書面選課 Registration will be done by paper application using the form generated from the system.','全18週',1141,'11870','3','專業選修(系所)','6','3,4','','A0',1),('2331','論文專題研究III','Dissertation Independent Study III','','','修課限制：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English. \n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1141,'11870','3','專業選修(系所)','6','6,7','','A0',1),('2332','博士論文II','Dissertation II','本課程以個別指導之形式，旨在協助博士生以臨床實務或護理專業發展為基礎，應用相關理論、照護模式及研究能力，執行研究計畫，進行資料分析，完成博士論文之撰寫。','This course is conducted through individualized instruction with the objective of assisting the doctoral student who is building upon his/her clinical practice or nursing professional development. It focuses on the application of relevant theories, nursing care models, and research skills, the execution of research projects, data analysis, and the completion of the dissertation.','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n3.本所國際博士班可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (doctoral level)\n 4.書面選課 Registration will be done by paper application using the form generated from the system.','全18週',1141,'11870','4','專業必修(系所)','6','3,4','','A0',6),('2333','高等生物應用統計學','Advanced Applied Biostatistics','本課程以教授研究所學生具有進階應用生物統計學的分析能力。強調生物統計學之應用與醫學及護理臨床研究結合，以奠定學生具有資料收集、資料分析及統計報表解讀之能力，同時有能力評值學術期刊所發表的文章。課程內容包括：基本機率論、機率分佈理論、統計估計及檢定(獨立樣本及成對樣本t-test)、變異數分析(ANOVA)、相關係數、簡單迴歸分析到複迴歸分析等議題。本課程將會使用SPSS等專業統計軟體之操作。','Biostatistics plays an essential role in all stages of a quantitative health care research from design through to analysis and interpretation. This course covers the essential principles and methods required for a master degree. Emphasis is on study design, appropriate analysis, software application (SPSS) and interpretation of results. The underlying concepts of statistical analysis are covered. Sessions include lectures and practical work, both computer-based and using small workshops for discussion.\r\nThe course aims to teach health care researchers the essential elements of research methodology and statistics. The focus is mainly on interpretation and understanding appropriate methodology.','修課限制Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.與助產所國際碩士班合開 Co-offered with the International Midwifery program. \n3.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n4.本所國際碩士班、助產所國際碩士班、本所國內碩士班一年級可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level), students of the International Midwifery program, and first-year students of domestic master\'s programs in nursing.','全18週',1141,'11860','1','專業必修(系所)','3','2,3,4','F603','A0',3),('2334','健康評估及實驗','Health Assessment for Advanced Practice Nursing','本課程旨在增強學生臨床實務相關評估之學理與技巧。課程內容著重於應用病史訪談、心理與生理評估技巧、詮釋評估結果於各年齡層之個案。學生須針對個案之個別性，應用相關學理與技巧，進行評估、分析與診斷個案健康問題，以達成課程的目標。','The purpose of the course is to advance students’ physical assessment theory and skills that related to professional clinical nursing practice. The content of the course is emphasized on application skills of client interview, physiological and psychologi','修課限制 Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English.\n2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools.\n3.本所國際碩士班、本所國內碩士班一年級可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level) and first-year students of domestic master\'s programs in nursing','全18週',1141,'11860','1','專業必修(系所)','4','6,7,8,9','B517','A0',3),('2335','專題研究','Independent Study','','','修課限制 Course restrictions ：\n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English.\n2.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools.\n3.本所國際碩士班可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level). \n4.書面選課 Registration will be done by paper application using the form generated from the system.','全18週',1141,'11860','1','專業選修(系所)','6','1,2','','A0',1),('2336','護理理論','Nursing Theory','本課程旨在培養學生應用護理理論於實務、研究、教育和行政中之能力。主要學習經驗包括探討護理理論發展史、理論家背景、理論的重要概念及其闡述的現象、理論的應用。在引導下，學生深入研討至少一個護理理論，透過相關文獻的分析、歸納和演譯，練習將整合後的心得和經驗提出報告與同學分享、討論以達成本課程的目標。','This course examines several nursing concepts and their applications to the current health care environment including practice, education, administration, and research. Students begin to recognize the nature of science and its relationships to theories in nursing. Through discussion, lecture, and specially designed projects, students will learn the philosophy and background of a theorist and her/his theory and develop skills in analyzing health care issue, particularly those with relevance to nursing.','修課限制 Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.與助產所國際碩士班合開 Co-offered with the International Midwifery program. \n3.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n4.本所國際碩士班、助產所國際碩士班、本所國內碩士班一年級可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level), students of the International Midwifery program, and first-year students of domestic master\'s programs in nursing.','全18週',1141,'11860','1','專業必修(系所)','5','3,4','G104','A0',2),('2337','統計資料管理與分析策略','Data Management &amp; Statistical Analysis','本科目於教學設計上，乃著眼於資料庫管理與統合各種量性資料分析方法之實務操作，目標在於提昇學生管理與分析統計相關資料之能力。課程中將運用SPSS統計套裝軟體來學習以下統計資料管理與分析策略：1)建立資料庫檔案並進行資料庫檔案之增刪、編輯與修改；2)著手分析健康照護相關之研究資料、繪製資料圖表;3)運用描述性與推論性統計策略;4)撰寫研究資料之分析結果。整體而言，選修本課程之學生，將透過課程講授、實際練習操作統計套裝軟體及實例研討等方法，落實學習統計資料之管理與分析。','The objective of this course is to provide students with practical applications of bio-statistical methods by running the SPSS statistical software. Two sample data (depression data and factor analysis data) in the health related agendas will demonstrate',' 修課限制 Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.與助產所國際碩士班合開 Co-offered with the International Midwifery program. \n3.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n4.本所國際碩士班、助產所國際碩士班、本所國內碩士班一年級可選 Eligible students include students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level), students of the International Midwifery program, and students of domestic master\'s programs in nursing.','全18週',1141,'11860','2','專業選修(系所)','1','6,7,8','F603','20',3),('2338','國際健康政策與實務','International Health Policy and Practice','本課程旨在提供有關國際健康政策相關議題的概述,協助護理學生以全球化觀點了解未來的執業環境.課程內容包括:國際與全球健康,影響健康的相關因素探討,國內外相關資源,不同地理區域的健康問題,健康疾病指標,以及國際健康未來趨勢.','This course is designed to provide introductory content in international health and nursing useful for all level of health care students who will be practicing in the era of globalization, regardless of whether they personally plan to live or work. The th','修課限制 Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English. \n2.與助產所國際碩士班合開 Co-offered with the International Midwifery program. \n3.不開放跨校選課 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools. \n4.本所國際碩士班二年級、助產所國際碩士班二年級、本所國內碩士班二年級可選 Eligible second-year students include students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level), second-year students of the International Midwifery program, and second-year students of domestic master\'s programs in nursing.\"','全18週',1141,'11860','2','專業選修(系所)','3','2,3,4','G103','21',3),('2339','實證健康照護與應用','Evidence-based health-care and Application','本課程主要協助學生瞭解護理之實證研究與實證實務，期使學生能在實證之理論與研究上有所認識，而應用於臨床有關健康照護，以增進學生健康照護之護理實證實務能力。課程內容包含實證相關之理論與研究以及實務層面，例如臨床決策之評量、質量性研究之評量、實證研究問題之發展、發展搜尋策略、研究品質之評量、發展實證護理研究計畫等。','This course provides students to have the concepts of evidence-based nursing for research and practice in healthcare. The major focus of the course encompasses the understanding of the issues about evidence-based research and practical application through the participation, presentation, and discussion in the class.','修課限制Course restrictions ：\n1.全英語授課 This class is taught in English.\n2.不開放跨校 Not open to students from other universities.','全18週',1141,'11860','2','專業選修(系所)','3','6,7,8','B603','22',3),('234','服務學習','Service Learning','本課程設計旨在協助學生培養服務的精神，藉由至服務機構提供服務，落實課堂所學之服務知識與理念，並進而從服務中學習、瞭解服務於社區之重要性與體驗服務之意義，培養正向的服務態度，以期自我省思、瞭解自我進而促進自我成長與肯定生命價值。','This course is provided to introduce the basic concepts of volunteer, and help the students with fundamental understanding in non-profit organization (NPO). The class will be guided by different instructions of lecture, group discussion, homework and test','修課限制：本系四技一般生','全18週',1132,'21140','1','專業必修(系所)','1','5','G103','A0',0),('2340','進階護理II','Advanced Practice Nursing II','','This course is aimed to increase students\' understanding of the major concepts and related theories \r\nof advanced practice nursing. The focus is on the management of mental health issues as well as the \r\ncommunity health. The course will provide students with fundamental knowledge necessary to \r\ndeliver advanced nursing care for clients with mental health conditions as well as for clients in the \r\ncommunity settings. The roles and function of advance practice nurses will be integrated throughout \r\nthe course. Through lectures, discussions, and reports, students will expand their knowledge and \r\ncompetency for managing common mental health issues and community health by integrating \r\nevidenced-based nursing and their clinical experiences.','修課限制 Course restrictions ： \n1.全英語授課 Taught entirely in English.\n 2.不開放跨校 Not open for cross-registration with students from other schools.\n 3.本所國際碩士班碩二以上可選 Eligible students include second-year and higher-level students of the International Nursing program (master\'s level)','全18週',1141,'11860','2','專業必修(系所)','1','2,3,4','B128','A0',3),('2341','臨床藥理及治療學','Clinical Pharmacology &amp; Therapeutics','本課程之設計係以護理研究所碩士班學生為授課對象。課程內容著重目前有關心血管藥理、癌症治療等方面之進展為主，並探討相關藥物之藥理作用機轉與目前臨床應用有關之藥物資訊等，故使用之教材係取自較新之期刊論文，目的是讓學生對於最近之醫藥相關科學之發現與進展能獲得最新資訊。','This elective course is designed for nursing students at the graduate level. It emphasizes the pharmacological mechanisms and clinical application of the agents commonly prescribed in disease teratment. Topics in this course include drugs acting on cardio','修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、老人組、婦女組、精神組、社區組、兒童組、護資組、專師組、中西醫組）','全18週',1141,'11462','1','專業選修(系所)','6','6,7,8','G403','10',3),('2342','健康促進與管理','Health promotion and management','本課程主要協助學生瞭解健康促進與管理之實務層面與其相關研究，期使學生能在健康促進與管理之理論與實務有所認識，而應用於臨床有關健康促進與管理層面之照護，以增進學生健康照護之能力。課程內容包含健康促進與管理相關之理論與研究以及實務層面之見習，例如：健康促進與管理之相關理論、體重管理之機轉，評值、體重過重與過輕對健康之影響，與疾病相關之影響、兒童肥胖與更年期肥胖、各種健康管理之策略、臨床健康管理週課程見習。','This course provides students to have the basic concepts of health promotion and management for health care. The major focus of the course encompasses: Introduction(Prevalence, evaluation of body composition) Etiology and health impact of obesity and underweight Obesity related disease: Metabolic syndrome, health management related problem in menopausal women, Health problems in Abnormal weight during childhood, Clinical approach of weight management, Nutritional strategies of weight management , Exercise strategies of management , Comparison of variant diet of health promotion and management: evidence based approach Visiting clinics 1(including exercise practice and diet preparation practice) ,Obesity treatment: medical, surgical and herbal preparation , Behavior approach of health promotion and management, E-health management. Students present their understanding of the health issues about health promotion and management through the participation and discussion in the class.','修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、老人組、婦女組、精神組、社區組、兒童組、護資組、專師組、中西醫組）、本系國內博士班、外所國內碩博士班（是否列入畢業學分，請參照入學年課程科目表）','全18週',1141,'11462','1','專業選修(系所)','4','11,12,13,14','G204','11',3),('2343','高等生物統計學','Advanced Biostatistics','本課程旨在介紹高等生物統計學之廣義線性模式分析方法、實用觀念、探討應用以及可行之技巧及工具，引導學生操作或使用SPSS和SAS等分析工具。透過本課程之講授和練習，可讓學生具備對廣泛醫學資料之模式分析能力，進一步能夠批判文獻、評估研究設計及相關推論之效能，並運用於工作之專業上。修讀本課程需先具備基本之流行病學概論及生物統計學基礎。','The focus of this course is applied statistical techniques, with emphasis on data management, and data analysis through the Statistical Package for the Social Sciences. This course will complete weekly computer assignments that provide \"hands on\" experience with data analysis and interpretation of results. Students will actually understand statistical procedures and apply statistical techniques to concrete data.','修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、專師組）、程式設計課程','全18週',1141,'11462','1','專業必修(系所)','5','12,13','F603','A0',2),('2344','健康評估及實作','Health Assessment for Advanced Practice Nursing','本課程旨在增強學生臨床實務相關評估之學理與技巧。課程內容著重於應用病史訪談、心理與生理評估技巧、詮釋評估結果於各年齡層之個案。學生須針對個案之個別性，應用相關學理與技巧，進行評估、分析與診斷個案健康問題，以達成課程的目標。','The purpose of the course is to advance students\' physical assessment theory and skills that related to \r\nadvanced nursing practice. The content of the course is emphasized on application skills of client \r\ninterview, physiological and psychological assessment, interpreting results in individuals. This course \r\nfocuses on development of clinical decision making skills in the process of health assessment. Applying \r\ntheories and techniques, assessing, analyzing and diagnosing health problems on selected clients. As \r\none outcome of this course, students demonstrate comprehensive and integrative health assessment \r\npractice and written skills.','修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、精神組、社區組）','全18週',1141,'11462','1','專業必修(系所)','5','6,7,8,9','B414','A0',3),('2345','護理理論','Nursing Theories','本課程旨在培養學生應用護理理論於實務、研究、教育和行政中之能力。主要學習經驗包括探討護理理論發展史、理論家背景、理論的重要概念及其闡述的現象、理論的應用。在引導下，學生深入研討至少一個護理理論，透過相關文獻的分析、歸納和演譯，練習將整合後的心得和經驗提出報告與同學分享、討論以達成本課程的目標。','This course examines several nursing concepts and their applications to the current health care environment including practice, education, administration, and research. Students begin to recognize the nature of science and its relationships to theories in','修課限制：本所碩士班（成人組、社區組）','全18週',1141,'11462','1','專業必修(系所)','5','10,11','G204','A0',2),('2346','國際進階護理實務','','','','授課期間：07/01-07/31暑期授課。不開放選課，僅限學海築夢美國華盛頓大學醫學中心交流計畫同學有選課資格。修課限制：EMI全英語授課、本所碩士班（成人組、老人組、婦女組、精神組、社區組、兒童組、護資組、專師組、中西醫組）、提前開課','第1週',1141,'11462','2','專業選修(系所)','6','13','','20',1),('2347','成人專科護理 II','Adult Practice Nursing II','本課程旨在培育成人專科護理師學生具備急性醫療特定疾病病人之進階知識與技能，並加強其對對專科護理師角色、功能與執業議題之瞭解。課程強調運用批判性思維與實證醫學和護理，以建立適當之健康問題診斷、處置和評價照護結果之學習。透過講述、學生課堂導讀、案例分析、小組討論、角色扮演、影片情境分析與數位平台討論等多元教學策略，訓練學生批判性思考、溝通與自學能力，並培養學生具備成人專科護理師入門所需之知識與技能，使其能以專科護理師的角色提供急性醫療特定疾病病人適切之進階護理照護。','This course provides the student with in-depth knowledge of advanced nursing management of complicated and acutely ill adults. Emphasis is on the utilization of critical thinking and evidence-based practice to formulate diagnoses and management and evaluation plans of care for physiologically unstable and complicated adult patients who have multiple complex health problems, and are at high risk for developing complications.  The focus is on the management of specific system problems of acute care. This course provides students with advanced knowledge necessary to deliver advanced nursing care in acute care settings.','08/04暑期提前授課，修課限制：本所碩士班（專師組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11468','2','專業必修(系所)','5','2,3,4','F501','A0',3),('2348','成人專科護理實習 II','Adult Practice Nursing II - Practicum','本課程旨在培育成人專科護理師學生，具備急性醫療嚴重病人照護之進階知識與技能，並加強其對對專科護理師執業議題之瞭解。實習課程強調運用批判性思維與實證醫學和護理，以建立適當之健康問題診斷、處置和評價照護結果於所照護之個案。透過實習契約書之訂定、實習指導教師與實習教學教師的共同輔導、實習日誌、個案報告、互動記錄、臨床照護指引、教案與實習心得的完成，以確保學生的實習經驗，至實習結束每位學生將至少照護十位內外科急性醫療嚴重病人，以培養學生具備成人專科護理師所需之知識與技能，使其能以專科護理師的角色提供病情嚴重之急性醫療病人適切之進階護理照護。','The course is a continuum of the clinical practicum for adult health nursing I. The purposes of the course are (1) to train students’ competencies in assessing, diagnosing, examining, and managing common medical and surgical health problems, (2) to facilitate students’ consultation ability for emotional responses of acute ill patients, (3) to cultivate students’ case management ability, (4) to increase students’ communication and collaboration to achieve excellent care, and (5) to be familiar with ethical and legal issues affecting NP practice in Taiwan.. Within the practicum, student will demonstrate actual roles and responsibilities of an acute care nurse practitioner.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（專師組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11468','2','專業必修(系所)','7','5','','A0',3),('2349','老人健康照護 II','Health Care of Elderly II','此課程旨在透過對老人健康照護政策、管理、策略及社區發展的理論、研究與議題研討，增進學生對老人照護相關之管理、領導、教育、諮商等能力。學生需統整及應用老人健康照護、經濟、主要照顧者、社會支持、組織發展等理論研究於實務情境中，發揮其個案管理及團體照護之功能，並需獨立針對特定議題完成專案以展現其老人照顧專家的角色功能，並展現其統合資源建立社區網絡之能力。','This course is designed to cultivate students’ abilities on management, leadership, education, and consultant of elder care services, based on the theories of elder policy, management, strategy, and community development. Students have to integrate the theories of elder health, economy, caregiver, social support, organizational development, etc., and apply into the real situations. Students are expected to express the roles and function of case management and group care, to implement and evaluate health care project for elder groups, and to synthesis community resources.','授課時間：08:30-11:20，修課限制：本所碩士班（老人組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11462','2','專業必修(系所)','5','1,2,3,4','G204','A0',3),('235','健康科技導論','Introduction to Health Technology','本課程先介紹有關休閒產業、健康事業、健康科技照護以及語言治療與聽力障礙的發展趨勢，並了解目前各領域科技應用的現況及跨領域之可能性，內容包括保健旅遊之跨域整合、管理方法應用、資訊科技與長照領域之結合，以及聽語治療的應用等。藉由各領域發展趨勢的了解，進一步透過企劃案構思，讓學生能充分了解跨領域應用的精隨。','This course introduces the development trends of leisure and health industry, healthcare technology, and speech language pathology and audiology. The course also briefs the current state of technology applications, and identifies the possibility of cross-domain integration that includes the domains on health tourism, management, information technology, the long-term care, and speech language pathology and audiology. Based on the understanding of cross-domain background, students can propose business plan to fulfill the requirement of cross-domain applications on healthcare domain.','修課限制：健科學院四技一般生。健科學院四技一年級生不開放換班，如有特殊加退選需求請洽健科學院。','全18週',1132,'21140','1','專業必修(系所)','1','6,7','G103','A0',2),('2350','老人健康照護實習 II','Health Care of Elderly II -Practicum','此課程旨在透過對老人健康照護政策、管理、策略及社區發展的理論、強化臨床\r\n批判思考能力於老人相關研究與議題研討，增進學生對老人照護相關之管理、領\r\n導、教育、諮商及決策判斷等能力。學生需統整及應用老人健康照護、經濟、主\r\n要照顧者、社會支持、組織發展等理論研究於實務情境中，發揮其個案管理及團\r\n體照護之功能，並需獨立針對特定議題運用批判思考完成專案報告以展現其老人\r\n照顧專家的角色功能並能增進學生統合資源建立社區網絡之能力。','This course in designed to assist students acquiring ageing health policy, administration, strategy theory in the community nursing care of aging population. In this course, students are required self-direction learning, and will join an organization in community, interest to special issue and demonstrate the role functions of case manager in appropriate clinical settings.','修課限制：實習課程、本所碩士班（老人組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11462','2','專業必修(系所)','7','5','','A0',3),('2351','兒童健康照護 II','Health Care of Children (II)','本課程在協助學生發展照顧由醫療機構至社區中具有健康問題兒童之進階護理能力。藉由相關理論及實證研究，探討不同發展階段中，具有特殊需求或高危險兒童所處的環境〈如：家庭、學校、社區〉對兒童生長發展的長期影響。內容並強調現有的醫療體系/健康政策、及社會資源與兒童及其家庭成員之間的相互影響，並從中思考所衍生的倫理議題。學生最終能具備統整知識及資源的能力並積極為個案及其家庭代言。','This course will explore the potential and existing issues derived from the children with health problems in the community. Based on the relevant theories and evidence based research findings, students will be able to 1) analyze the mutual influences among the children with health problems, their ecological systems and related health policies/ resources, 2) organize the client’s resources and develop effective plans in the care of children with health problems, and 3) act as advocates for the children when encountering the ethical issues.','修課限制：本所碩士班（兒童組）研二以上','全18週',1141,'11466','2','專業必修(系所)','5','2,3,4','B6021','A0',3),('2352','兒童健康照護實習 II','Clinical practicum in Health Care of Children (II)','本課程旨在協助學生發展持續性且完整性的進階護理能力，提供個案及其家庭由醫療機構延續至社區中之照顧；藉由相關理論及實證研究，探討不同發展階段中，具有特殊需求或高危險兒童所處的環境〈如：家庭、學校、社區〉對其生長發展的長期影響。內容並強調現有的醫療體系/健康政策、及社會資源與兒童及其家庭成員之間的關係，並從中思考所衍生的倫理議題。學生能統整並運用知識及資源提供完整及持續性的照護。','This course is designed to assist students acquiring clinical expertise in the care of children with special needs or children at risk. Students are required to select an interested area to practice. By thoroughly assessing and analyzing the client’s situation (health, environment, health policies and resources), students will integrate the evidence based knowledge and provide the continuity care to the family of a child with special needs or at risk. The practices of self-directed learning, problem solving and critical thinking skills are highly expected in this course.','修課限制：本所碩士班（兒童組）研二以上、實習課程','全18週',1141,'11466','2','專業必修(系所)','7','5','','A0',3),('2353','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（精神組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1141,'11464','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('2354','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（兒童組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1141,'11466','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('2355','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授，修課限制：本所碩士班（社區組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1141,'11465','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('2356','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完成研究計畫之書寫。','This course is delivered in an individualized format, tailored to the nursing specialization and future professional development of the master\'s student. It guides students in exploring relevant core concepts and theories, integrating their clinical expertise, applying critical thinking and evidence-based nursing concepts, determining research directions and topics, and developing research designs, culminating in the completion of a research proposal.','授課時間地點請洽指導教授。修課限制：本所碩士班（護資組在職生）、書面選課','全18週',1141,'11467','2','專業選修(系所)','7','1','','A0',1),('2357','專題研究','Independent Study','本課程以個別指導之形式，依據碩士生之護理專長背景及未來專業發展方向，引導學生探索相關核心概念、理論，結合其臨床專業技能，應用批判性思考及實證護理的概念，訂定研究方向及主題，擬定研究設計、完